- create git account
- create repo in web console
- install git bash (if you are using windows) - by default git will be installed in Linux os
generate the ssh keys
push your id_rsa.pub to git account
clone the repos which you have created in console
add new files
add the file using git command in your local
push the changes



- create 2 different git account or ask your friend to create git project in git porta
- create code in your friend git account
- create fork to your friend repository
- do the necessary changes
- create PR from your account to your friend account
- ask your friend to approve the changes or close the PR
